{"text": "I am a huge fan of roguelikes. They are my favorite genre by far, which means I am very critical. Dead Cells is a perfect roguelike. It is difficult, but passable, it has many different build paths at every stage of the game, and the progression system is rewarding and makes you want to play MORE. The controls are smooth, the visuals consist of some of the best pixel art I have ever seen, and it is really, really fun. I am just starting to figure this game out, and it's gotten me more hyped then ever to see where this masterpiece can take me.", "appid": "588650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198127204021", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1532088000.0}
