{"text": "TL;DR 9/10 for sure! If you enjoy sandbox RPG games then you'll love this one. Easily the KING of sandbox rpg games. Tons of cool features and spells, Weapons and armor. Here's just a list of what I could pull from my head of pros and cons. Pros: Cool Items Magic works in a neat way Bosses are challenging and fun to farm Has Expert mode (Even more items) Has a modding Community thats alive and well Tons of replayability and different play styles Cons: Vanilla game once played alot can get stale Some bosses are OP Game is 32 bit. (Seriously devs add 64bit support please.) Game does not support IPV6 and as such can not host if you don't have dedicated IPV4. No Modding Support (Steam Workshop) Overall with all the stuff in this game, It surprises me how after 400+hours i can still find things i never knew existed. Plus with mods, It just adds even more content. If you get this, I highly suggest you play it through to completion at least once before going to get mods. And if you do get mods, Be sure to try ones like Calamity, Tremor, or better yet... Thorium.", "appid": "105600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018240066", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "111", "votes_funny": "9", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573646400.0}
