{"text": "Jack-In-A-Castle is a whimsical visual novel set in a land of toys. It's cute, with an interesting storyline and BxB romances. There are three potential romances and 9 (+1 quick) endings. +Pros+ +Cute, storybook-like art +Interesting Toyland setting +Nice plotlines and 3 BxB romances(love interests affected the story and endings but didn't completely replace plot) +Interesting, sassy, and adorable characters with some witty banter (especially between Bunnie and Jack) +Very few to no grammatical or spelling errors! -Cons- -The music was okay and fit the scenes, but wasn't especially memorable -It's probably just me, but even with 30 save spots (split into five pages) I still didn't feel like it was enough. But then again, I save a lot in visual novels, so that's just my experience. Â¯\\_(ãƒ„)_/Â¯ In summary, Jack-in-A-Castle is a casual mystery/fantasy/romance VN with BxB romance that reminded me of a cute storybook. I enjoyed the storyline, it was a nice reading experience. I'd recommend it to VN, fantasy, choices matters, and story-rich fans.", "appid": "1080790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198211520780", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "23", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563019200.0}
