{"text": "Depth Hunter 2 is a decent little indie game about snorkeling under the water. Its a ok game for being a underway swimming game and some nice touches here and there. The graphics in the game are nice and like the little details they do here and there. Thereâ€™s plenty of fish swimming around ranging from so reef fish all the way up to sharks and a Blue Whale on one mission. Mission wise the game is kinda short on that. Most of the missions, including the DLC's, are basicly all the same. You either hunt for a certain fish or spear as many as you can, look for treasure, or take pictures. On all the 3 base maps and the 2 DLC's thatâ€™s basicly what you do. There will be a 2-4 missions that will have you stump for a bit on what you need to find but once you get it done, its a cake walk after that. If you do all the missions and don't do free dives, you'll have the game done in hour and a half to two hours. You can upgrade your character, which is a balded head man with no option to change your character, and have him swim better, spear better, and take a lot of pics. Once you done all the missions you can tackle the achievements and with the recent update, makes one of the achievements, Sharpshooter, basicly easy to get since you can hardly miss now. The maps are really detailed with you able to swim around a downed plane, a couple of ships, a sunken city, and a underwater trench. You can swim around as long as your oxygen holds out, which doubles as your health. You can swim right up to any fish and sharks and don't have to worry about getting attacked by any of them. So in short the game is fun and relaxing but gets very tedious and repetitive with the missions.", "appid": "248530", "steamid": "profiles/76561197980516374", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1413115200.0}
{"text": "So the real story is that the Vault Dweller instantly forgot his instructions, ran in fear from the rats that tried to bite him as soon as he stepped outside, tumbled across the wasteland, accidentally found a military base. Confused, freightened by the big creatures he just met and also probably dehydrated he fiddles with some device and blows up some hooded man in the process. Very embarassed by all of this, the awkward man he is, he decides it's best just to blow up the entire place and run away. So he tumbles south and just so happens to meet a bunch of folks who look exactly like all the guys he just blew up. Just so they don't find out what happened to their friends (it would be even more embarassing for him) he blows them up also. When this is done he rans back to his home to ask what he was supposed to do in the first place, but the overseer comes out and says \"you saved the world now gtfo\".ï»¿", "appid": "38400", "steamid": "profiles/76561197987665992", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1507464000.0}
