{"text": "240% completed and I hate this game so much definitely gonna finish all the DLC's then might play it again in a really far and far future. I really enjoy playing this game but also didn't like it at all. This game just has the worst story compare to previous games but at least some side quests are really good to play again on my Newgame+ playthrough. The real antagonist in this game is The f-ing Riddler like really? so annoying holy cow, you have to collect all of his trophies, solve all the riddles and destroy all destructible objects(but you do not need to do it again in Newgame+ thanks god!) in order to shut down 100% of crime in Gotham City(120% if you has the Season Of Infamy DLC) to witness the TRUE ENDING of the game which is not so impressive and definitely not worth it to do so. The characters in this game is what makes the game so memorable and I would love to fight side by side with Nightwing and Robin. Overall the gameplay is so much better and there are many new mechanics added like the Fear Multi-Takedown and you can now hit enemies while they lying on the ground without using the stupid ground takedown(RT+Y) which mostly break your combo in previous games because you can't counter while doing that. The Batmobile/Tank thing is out of place but I really like to participate in a tank battle whenever I can. And what completed the game 100% for 2 times give you? An exact upgraded batsuit at the beginning with a golden bat symbol(what a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ joke). Fans of Batman need to buy and play this game but do not expect too much because it's kind of a disappointment to me.", "appid": "208650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084695225", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1555156800.0}
