{"text": "This game is simply gorgeous. The graphics and sounds are rich and immersive. Gameplay is true to the franchise and if you like previous Tomb Rider titles you can't go wrong on this one. There's everything: strange places to explore, tombs and corpses, lurking enemies and dangerous animals, just like the good old times. this time a very light RPG-like skill point system lets you choose and refine your tomb-riding abilities. No swimming or riding vehicles in this one, but you get a bow which is very fun to use. Lara has become more human and the environment more real and unforgiving. The story won't win an Oscar soon but is not bad either. I find this last step in the franchise evolution a solid one, and even deserving a sequel. Tomb Rider is playable in a wide range of systems due to its spec flexibility. MP is a weakness but not as they want you to believe. A bit laggy, a bit confusing and lacking players, the maps are interesting and the weapons accept some grade of customization. Download all single player content (minus cheats) and don't get the rest until you have actually tried MP. Most is aesthetic, and the Hitman guns unecessary.", "appid": "203160", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071433169", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1373803200.0}
