{"text": "This game takes place in Siberian Russia. Domestic terrorists use explosives to derail a train, then attempt to kill any survivors regardless of class or political standing. The gameplay focuses on surviving the harsh environment, wolf/bear attacks, and being found by the renegades. There are three character types based on Russian politics during the early 1917: aristocracy, revolutionary, and neutral. Some characters literally have a \"socialist\" trait and thus strongly oppose Czar Nikolai II of the Romanovs. There are also several references to the Bolsheviks, though, oddly, Vladimir Lenin is not mentioned. Each character also has a secret, but will only reveal it if their trust in their comrades (fellow survivors) is high enough. Having the characters work together to survive builds up trust, friendship, and credit. The challenge is that there must be an aristocrat and revolutionary in the group, so they don't always get along.  : : I recommend it to anyone who enjoys strategy survival games or historical fiction ... or both!", "appid": "1119600", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067189801", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602417600.0}
