{"text": "This game is one of the most revolutionary games of the century. Not only does it have cunning graphics and engaging gameplay, but is a true modern art form that can easily be related to Picasso and Vincent van Gogh. Garfield Kart acts as a basis in which all games in the future shall follow. I call for Garfield Kart to be added as the 11th commandment as it is a game and world we all shall follow. I can highly recommend this game to anyone, the rich, poor, and working class as this game can appeal to anyone in any outreach of the world. Why, this game should be displayed 24/7 on a screen in Times Square, for all to see and enjoy as everyone should have at least 12% of their daily diet being lasagna. Our government leaders and representatives shall play this game as well, as it will increase the chances they start a Garfield Kart Fund and a Lasagna Fund. Although I now have to conclude this review, I do not know where to end. This game simply cannot be described in a paragraph... or with words for that matter. It shall be explained through easily interpreted body and hand movements along with the soothing sound of a cat chewing lasagna. However, this review must come to a slow and sickening end. My final statement on the matter is this: this game is not worth five dollars... It is worth the life of a cat and his lasagna, worth the world. If you do not enjoy this game, there is simply something wrong and you need to contact your doctor immediately for support. All show your support for this flawless and innovative game and let it live on!", "appid": "362930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198196836466", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1484222400.0}
