{"text": "Verdant Skies In Verdant Skies you crash on an alien planet \"Viridis Primus\" with some colonists. As you signed a contract with a big company you will need to work off your debts, let's say. As time is progressing you will get more tasks/quests to fullfill, more buildings to build, more blue prints to unlock and so on. Your main goal will be to farm on this planet and earn money. With this money you can buy a lot of stuff, which you can buy and build more of other items.  . It's a rather average to big planet area, where you can farm on different spots, mine in 2 caves, collect a lot of different stuff, like plants, rocks, scrap metal and so on. One of the important goals or topics in this game is genetic engineering of crops and animals.  . Overall is the atmosphere in this game very nice and the music is not annoying. I read on dev's webpage that there are almost 40.000 lines of dialog! Is this game grindy? To a certain degree yes, but show me a farming sandbox RPG without grinding. The goal in this game is to farm, talk with people and collect a lot of stuff. And this game does it very good! I liked the rising difficulty to get some materials, but at any point you can get any material with hard work or time, there were no bugs which prevented this and i encountered almost no bugs and no crashes at all. Some negative points were: the farming spots are far away from each other, a lot of walking even with  . Sapphire is hard to get in the start and scrap metal you can only get from collecting on ground, not buying. Overall is the gameplay fluid, every day you check your route, collect stuff and prepare new items. This rating system is my personal opinion and not to be intended to replace a professional rating system in any way! Rating (% * X / 100, sum of all as final rating X/10) My personal rating is  You ever wanted to build a community and farm on an alien planet? Then immerse in this beautiful adventure where you meet unique characters, date around the clock, start a family and farm off the crops till you faint. If you liked the review you can follow us as curator: and/or join our group:", "appid": "730050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198125567580", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "30", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543665600.0}
