{"text": "And it is super hard to talk about it, but I will try my best. To me many games that tried to expand and explore what games can really be, usually felt either forced (trying too hard) or less like a game and more like a somewhat interactive art piece. The Witness is different. It is a game and it is an awe-inspiring art piece at the same time and not as two separate aspects or layers, but as an interwoven whole. No game ever before, had such a strong effect on me as The Witness. When I finally figured out what it is really about, what it wants from me, when I fully understood the main mechanic, I was in shock, my heart was beating like crazy. Finding something I didn't know could even exist. It is really much more than meets the eye. I should also say it is one difficult to love piece. If you are not really into puzzle or calm and slow exploration games it may easily bore you to death or you may find it infuriatingly difficult at times. It tries really hard to alleviate these problems with its looks and level/puzzle design, but fails in some cases. One could easily stop playing even after long hours of trying due to not really finding enjoyment.", "appid": "210970", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993963771", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529496000.0}
