{"text": "Wonderful game :) At first you think the graphic is not good and so on, but you still feel like you're in the game, even if it's 2D pixel graphic.. and over the time if you meet all characters you take them into your heart, you want to know how their stories ends. On Nexus you can finds thousands mods and you can play it like you want. I played it with someone (coop) and it was really fun. I absolutely recommend it for everyone who likes farming games with little stories.", "appid": "413150", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992130737", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "35", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603108800.0}
{"text": "Catherine is a very good game intended as a metaphor to the dilemma caused during early stages of adulthood and the decisions that are made in one's love-life. It is rich in story and is said in a very mature manner. Platforming in the game is not like any other game. It is unique and very interesting to solve puzzles in each stage. Soundtrack is excellent and is apt as per the situation. It took me a good 20 hours to finish the main story with 1 of the 8 possible endings on Normal mode. There's a mini-game at the bar called Rapunzel which is a smaller version of the game itself. It can be played as a game too.  The character development of the protagonist in the game is well written and we can choose how his character develops by the various decisions we take across the course of game.  Overall, Catherine Classic is a game worth playing for anyone who enjoys interesting story-telling and platforming.", "appid": "893180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198237367450", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588766400.0}
