{"text": "What a game. Before I start this review, just buy it. This game is almost perfect in my opinion. I play this game on controller, and it is clear that the developers haven't just ignored more casual players, even though this is definitely a simulator rather than a casual game (not that you can't play it casually). The controls feel great, nothing to complain about here. My system is a 4690k with 8gb ram, and the game ran great on my 960 2g, and runs amazingly on my new vega 56. The one thing that is important to keep in mind when playing the game is that it is OK to not come first. Once you get over this, and think about it as improving rather than winning (e.g.: you are often coming 6th, and start moving up to 5th and 4th), the game becomes a lot more enjoyable. Overall: Stages: 10/10 Cars (sound and graphics): 10/10 Handling/controls: 10/10 Would rally again 10/10", "appid": "310560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198156196072", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538568000.0}
