{"text": "Alright so I bought played and finishes Assassin's Creed Liberation and this is what I think about it. The protagonist - Aveline De Grandpre is an interesting character but atleast in my opinion the voice actor did not do a very good job voiceing it. The other thing is that the game is not optimized properly I have a decent machine and the game came out in 2012 but it was not running the way it suppose to. There are a few audio bugs in the game wich is not awful or anything but that takes away a small piece away from the experience and the story is a tiny bit hard to follow even thou the game is quite short as usual the game has a lot of collectibles but still even though I got quite a few of them I finished the game under 10 hours. And the game itself has almost nothing to do with the main AC story line but the game is a spin off so I should not be harsh about that. So this is how I'm going to rate the game. Story - 5/10 Gameplay - 5/10 Graphics - 6/10 Overall - 16/30 Honestly this is the worst Assassin's Creed game I ever played (and I played majority of them) but still I got the game on sale for only a few bucks and I'm a hardcore AC series fan so I'm not sad that I bought but I would only reccomend this game for other huge franchise fans and if you are not then just save the money.", "appid": "260210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198074638066", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603627200.0}
