{"text": "A turn based roguelite that feels like:  +Dungeons of Dredmore combat (enemies move after you move) w/ Blinding of Issac like maps  +Enter the gungeon teleport map traversal so not too much backtracking & various risk/reward gambling loot rooms! +Work with what you have - randomized access to table of all spell lists, weapon types, consumables.  +Build your character based on starting weapon/spell combos with currency carryover on death for upgrading future runs +Extremely good UI, colorful graphics for inventory, options, clear layout of character & damage stats.  As a fan of dungeons of dredmore, sword of the stars the pit, tangle deep this game is easy to pick up with decent variety of weapon/spell combos that gives plenty of risk reward events. Also has really good mouse/keyboard options.  I could easily see this game polish with more difficult fine balances for veteran players. New modes, challenges etc. So much potential!", "appid": "1000010", "steamid": "profiles/76561198155044288", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "66", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602936000.0}
