{"text": "Suprise sleeper. Might be my GOTY for 2014.This game is amazing, the atmosphere, art style and music made it dificult for me to put down. It feels like a Creepy  Fairy Tale, made into an interactive Kid's book. I can honestly say, I don't think I've played a game quite like this. It's technically an adventure, but the way it's handle makes it feel like so much more than just that. Really unique and captivating, I'd recommmend it to anyone who hates Video games and thinks they are all the same crap...or someone who loves them, because this game is awesome. EDIT: Um, so there's also a REAL ending that involves codes, visuals, reading and clues...yeah 11/10", "appid": "269050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035396704", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1420372800.0}
