{"text": "> started third playthrough > returned to Pascal's village, child robots asked me to play with them > built them a slide with toy parts, they all look overjoyed > felt glad to see them running and sliding around their village, everything is okay [SPOILER ALERT] > literally back to the village 10 minutes later,the whole village was â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ burning >  dead robots everywhere, pascal and the children are nowhere to be seen >  pascal suddenly called, they flee the scene to an abandoned factory > arrived inside the factory. place was dark, grim, full of child robots cried over their dead parents > suddenly,  a horde of enemies is surrounding the factory [/spoiler] > fought the enemies with pascal, who swore an oath to protect the children no matter what  > enemies are defeated, the children are safe, returned inside the factory to check on them  > nope, they're dead. all of them. not from the enemies. death by suicide, their cores are wide open > pascal plunged into insanity, begged me to either kill him or wipe out his entire memory > my hands are shaking, I don't want to kill a pacifist so I chose the latter > returned to the village, now empty. The slide is still there though > pascal is standing alone, his memory is now gone, he tried to sell me something > he tried to sell me the children cores, saying \"it's all junk and I don't know what to do with them\" If that's not the most heart wrenching moment in video games, then I dont know what is", "appid": "524220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198179488025", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1521547200.0}
