{"text": "Six hours into the game and I had to pry myself away from it for the sake of this Review! YES! RAGE 2 is a fantastic power fantasy and a good game to get lost into. However, whether you want to get lost in its world depends on your preferences and what you should  look for in a game which is a sequel to an overly hyped game that was mostly hit and miss. I, from my initial expressions from the game wanted the following:  1.  . 2.  2.  3.  4.     5.    Things I thought would make the world cooler if they added to it were: 1.  2.    3.  and What I got was: 1.  : Gunplay is solid, it has got the kick to it that I have admired from DOOM 2016. The bullet impact on tweaked, cracked and drugged mutants and mercs is awesome. The variety of guns is present. However, surprises are not. I mean, you get the outline of most of the GOOD guns in the game right from the beginning. So, you have an idea of what you are going to get. Does it hinder the gunplay? HAIL NAW (I wrote it like this cuz apparently steam's review has gone to the dark ages)! Would it have been cooler to find goody-guns around in an OPEN world that you didn't know about, obviously!  2.  : There are many guns and many ways to pursue your missions. You want a fast in and out combat while you hide behind the guise of stylishness, you can. Want to feel like a tank you take on and give bullets like thanksgiving? You can. Want to create a human centipede midst combat through some specific gun? you can! From Flash bashing to shock-waves to crushing to Roy Mustanging someone's \"behind\", the combat options are many, and varied.  3.  : The Vehicular combat is a DIRECT, I mean a DIRECT COPY of Madmax. Although I wanted something more akin to Twisted Metal (a man can dare to dream), I was utterly contented with what I got. I mean, I dug MAD MAX, a  LOT. So I got no complaints there. However, I really hoped that this awesome vehicular combat was not that sparse. While there is enough of it, your vehicle won't have much to do other than racing for some long stretches. Considering the handling of the drunk hunk of turtle (trust me, initially, that is what the vehicles are), racing won't make you feel exhilarated, you would just be happy that its over with.  4.  : The power ups, although not many, can be upgraded in many different ways. There are upgrades for upgrades in this game. However, the drab and utterly disgusting menu screen did not particularly entice me to actually upgrade my skills, but I did, and I was satisfied.  5.  : There are many variety of locations in the game, but somehow, they look the same. They got variety, but I am just out of sobriety so I think most of them are lame. Don't get me wrong, the hub cities are cool, and that cool neon induced color palette makes the game like an 80's apocalypse movie, but other than hub cities, some underground tunnels, some Arks, the rest of exploration is kinda......meh! There are not many interesting things to find in the world other than more combat opportunities, more Feltrite, more auto core mods, more weapon core mods, more nano core mods, and well, more money.  6.  : It has a power fantasy element to it. You feel like a wasteland superhero like if the buffed dude from Fist of the North Star traded his fists for guns. Well, not really because unlike the Stoic \"Kenshiro\", walker likes to talk, a lot, and uselessly. But I digress, it gives you the power to be more powerful than your opponents. However, if you are playing at any difficulty which is less than hard, then your power fantasy might make you feel like a bumbling drunk crushing some insects. if you hit someone my accident then it can kill. And the AI, much like Rage 1 is not  the best. I really hopes that some of the Doom 2016's difficulty goodness would slide into Rage 2 but no, it didn't happen. On hard however, it got everything you can hope for. you need to be tactical, and enemy variety is enough to keep you engaged.  The characters are not particularly memorable, other than some key ones. However, it has more to do with the good designs of the key characters and not the dialogue itself. Character design other than some leading ones is not good.   So, we can safely say that what extra I wanted from this game that would have made it amazing, I did not get. However, is the game disappointing in anyway. â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ NO! But I say this because all I wanted was some good power fantasy, badass gunplay, amazing vehicular combat, power-ups, and locations and I got it all. I mean, I can say that I would have tweaked somethings in the game to make it more badass, but that is just me.  So, in conclusion, it is a good and addictive game. However, if you are shelling 60 bucks or in my case INR 3,999/-, you are going to expect something more. Curb your expectations a bit or the game will curb stomp your desire to play it. That said, if you go into the game with a doom mindset of \"effing some feces up\", you will be satisfied.  So, wait for sale, but definitely recommend.", "appid": "548570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198177260918", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557921600.0}
