{"text": "tl;dr: This is not the right tool for my group/our game. Maybe it is right for you (get unity instead though) I am a new DM and I purchased this tool to see if it was a good fit for a split in-person/online game that I started with my family. Unfortunately I've spent more time trying to figure out how to use this tool than I've spent trying to understand the basics of the game (which is kind of a lot of time already) and it seems to be more cumbersome than is necessary for what I need it for.  Pro: 1. I feel like there is so much included and if you already know what you are doing in your game system (5E for me) you can probably really take advantage of all the hidden bells & whistles.  2. The dice and chat system seem really well done. I love the idea of typing out messages in specific languages and only having the players that understand those languages being able to read them.  Indifferent: 1. All of the official content you want is available and on sale occasionally. For me this doesn't matter as much because I have all of the materials for the campaign I want to run in print already. 2. Most of the features seem like they are pretty well flushed out, but some seem overly complicated or hard to find. IMO most of the features provided can be done easier with pencil and paper... if you trust your remote players. Cons: 1. The price. $40 for a single license (that is on sale occasionally) that does not allow you to host games is crazy to me when there are free alternatives. On top of that you are still going to be spending 50-100% of the price for digital copies of the books. 2. The UI is the opposite of intuitive for me. It took me almost an hour to figure out how to get a map onto the VTT and then have it shared. I've spent a few hours trying to set up my first two sessions and I still do not understand most of the controls related to the map. 3. For the price you get shockingly few tokens. I had to resort to hunting down free 3rd party ones to try to use for pretty much everything... once i figured out how to import maps. There are too many cumbersome features for a new DM and shockingly few resources to actually use in your game (Very few maps/tokens/etc) included in your purchase. The tool complicates more things than it simplifies for me and we will be using a simpler, FREE, tool (roll20, as evil as they are).", "appid": "252690", "steamid": "profiles/76561197973607961", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "23", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603454400.0}
