{"text": "is a game, developed by  , that looks good and feels like a unique game. However, when I started playing, I had some issues that I could not overlook, and the game at a standpoint has not aged well in some areas. Thatâ€™s not to say that the game does not have good moments, as I did enjoy some of the things it offered.  The story takes place in an unnamed city where everything is controlled by the  . Some people just accepted it, however, some did not take too kindly to the fact that everything they do was being watched, while some accepted it. Those that were against   were labeled as criminals, and they now get their mail from  . You play as  , a  , tasked to delivering these messages, who is on the run from  , the cityâ€™s protection force. The story of   has good ideas, but is generally weak overall. We have a corrupt city, but we are not given any examples of it being corruption. The only thing we get is text messages saying it is. There is no world-building either, and we are not giving an idea on how everything operates. The character development is also not great either, yes we do learn that   has a sister, but thatâ€™s all we get. The other characters that are presented donâ€™t really do much and are just there to be characters as none of them develop either. To make matters worse, the game is only about six hours long and does not show much from it. The gameplay for   is its biggest problem, that the game has, as I came across many issues that plagued the game. I have issues with both the   controller and with the keyboard. The   controller has a problem on   where the game tells you to press the RB button. The main issue with this is that it does not work, as, when I press the RB button   will just turn around and fall over. With the keyboard my inputs will not respond at times when I press a button, and this would happen more then once.  This frustrated me as I would end up falling to my death quite often because I did the action correctly but the game did not register it. Especially when I tried to disarm enemies as I would get hit first before being able to disarm the enemy. To make matters worse you can get two shot with melee hits and then maybe get shot with all the damage you taken. Despite the buttons not working, I actually liked using the keyboard more than the controller because I actually ended up feeling more comfortable with it.  has the ability to go into  , which can slow down time and make it easier to do certain actions that may be a bit hard to do in time. The main issue I had with this is that I never really found a time to use this ability, because I was getting ready to do the action when I was jumping to a platform. The issue I had us that I am getting ready to press the button for a corresponding action, so I don't have time to press the button. Thatâ€™s not to say this ability is useless, as some people may find this ability useful, itâ€™s just I did not find any use for it. I should mention that the areas are confusing to navigate and while game did show you which way to go, it did not help all the time. There is no mini-map and you have to try and guess where to go so you donâ€™t waste your time trying to move on to the next area. The parkour in the game is actually pretty good and was well used. As a matter of fact, I will say that   has some of the best parkour elements in any game that I have played thus far. The only issue I have is the controls that I mentioned earlier in the review. Combat in   is clunky, you have a punch, a kick, and a disarm that you can use to help take down enemies. You will have to use a variety of moves, so you canâ€™t spam the same move over and over again. The thing with combat is that you can do just that and the enemies can't do much. If you are fighting someone one on one, you can take out the person fighting without any issue. When it comes to fighting people with guns, however, is where the problems start to lie. You will want to disarm the enemies who have them but you actually have to run up to them. Those enemies will probably deal a large chunk of damage to you or will kill you before you get the chance. You can pick up  and use guns but shooting will hinder your movement and is clunky. You are not given a count for the ammo in your gun, so if you run out during a firefight you are pretty much dead. Your aim is also quite slow and you will probably die before you get a chance to shoot back. The 3D art style for   have not aged well and donâ€™t really look appealing as everywhere you go is white, red, or blue but mostly white and some other colour. The cutscenes in the game are 2D animated and feel like a show you would find on   in the year 2007. This is an interesting take, as I liked how they were presented and they were animated very well. The game runs very smoothly in 60 FPS and can run on low-end PCs. The game was tested with a NVIDA GeForce GTX 1060 3GB, 16 GB of RAM storage, and AMD Ryzen 5 1500X Quad-Core Processor 3.50.     The soundtrack for Mirror's edge did not really stick out to me. That said, I did find one good song that I did enjoy, and that was  .   had some interesting elements going for it and looked fun to play. However, the controls, clunky combat and confusing areas make this game more of a chore to play. The game does have good parkour, but having a good parkour element does not make the game fun to play.   had promise but I just can't overlook it's flaws, it's sad as I really wantted to enjoy the game.", "appid": "17410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198148401542", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601294400.0}
