{"text": "Frustration Drive It really pains me to downvote this game. Why? Because it's good! Everything works really well  EXCEPT for the main 'dimension blinky' mechanics. I understand they were trying to spice things up and make the genre more interesting, bold move, but, it didn't pay off. The pros: Graphics, music, shooting mechanics - on point! I love it. Story? who cares? just shoot stuff! The cons: The main dimension switch mechanics, along with the rest of the mechanics they add later on like reverse shooting. Really easy to get confused and blink yourself into a wall for insta-death. Really easy to get confused between abilities and blink into insta-death when you actually wanted to reverse shoot. Distracting! Not in a fun 'oo I got to focus I've got this' way. Tons of crap going on both sides of the screen so while you're busy focusing on one side, the other dimension waves its hands at you to grab attention 'oo oo over here look!' Levels are very short.  Bosses are too easy. I like this game, I really do, but the core mechanics doesn't work, is distracting, frustrating and just kills the fun.", "appid": "394430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198020708554", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587470400.0}
