{"text": "Well, it's pretty.  The Match 3 puzzles are challenging.  And those are the things I like. I run through  energy points so fast, that It isn't worth the energy it takes just to get excited about playing a Match 3 game.  I mean, this is basically a cross between Panic Room and many other...scratch that... EVERY other *pretty* Match 3 on Steam.  I already play the Panic Room, but only because I enjoy Hidden Object games, not because I like hunting around for <days/weeks/however long> to find all the darn item I need in order to progress further in the ridiculous story!  I think the biggest factor in my decision not to recommend this game, is that the story isn't as good as Panic Room's.  I don't like 'collection' games, as a rule, so I will not have many in my active game folder.  This is one that won't remain.", "appid": "463060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034121429", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573128000.0}
{"text": "Maximum edition? More like maximum bugged port. I don't know what happened during development of this game. My best guess is they wanted to focus on a console market, and that's what all PC gamers got: A terrible port which has been downgraded in all departments compared to the first game. This is how Crytek wants to deal with high amount of piracy from their first Crysis: \"You're interested in our IP? Have a bag of â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ with Crysis 2 tagged onto it, since you're just going to pirate it anyway.\" I feel like the PC audience has been alienated here. There's just so many things that went wrong with developing this game. The game doesn't even want me to beat it cause like I wrote in my first paragraph, you will encounter both in-game bugs and technical bugs that  can result in crash to desktop. This edition of the game somehow manages to have more bugs than the leaked beta test. It controls like the first Crysis, however, your nano suit has been casualized only to carry OP mode, stealth, binoculars which are only used as a waypoint system to find ammo, and nightvision, which is only viable to use in like freaking 3 parts of the whole game. Gotta have something to support that console controller! The checkpoint system WILL drive you nuts. It rarely logs down your progress on your map and just seem to live breathe its own life. If you get a CTD during a map, enjoy being thrown all the way back to the beginning of the map. Avoid this, even if you liked the first game. It's not a PC game, it's a quick money grab to make up for all the cash they didn't earn with their first game. I hope you got this through the cheap EA bundle like me. I feel bad for anyone actually getting this for full price.", "appid": "108800", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998483458", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1392984000.0}
