{"text": "â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ do I went full retarded? Pretty much no, but actually I really enjoy the game. Yes, I mean it, the game its is really fun! No â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, its considered the \"Second Worst Game on Steam\" and hated by almost all critics, which Im not really gonna super defend this game because I have to agree on some stuff. The looting in the game itself is actually pretty fun, scaling from huge varieties of weapons, food, armor protection, backpacks, and such. Zombies are not really that much of intense feel like other triple A title zombie games, so expect some stupid â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ to happen. (and bugs...). In terms of PvP and PvE is not really this game main thing, since it mostly feels like \"Shoot first, ask question later\", if you can bare the killing survivors or avoiding them (or purchase your own private server), then you might get through this alive. Since the game is also F2P (but is only trials and you can get that on their site), there also consist of  different type of servers, Public server ( Obviously... ), Trial Server ( for F2P people ), Private Server ( for privater looters or just average host ), Public Test Server ( Test-out for their update on current map or new map ), Stronghold Server ( No announcement on it ) and the Veteran Server ( for players that played it above it 100 Hours ). *Theres another one but its just complete crap. You have litterally 5 Characters creator ( 1 if you are on Trial ), even they die you can pretty much revive them or instant respawn ( with In-game GC). Not much you can really create as you just pick few of the pre-made ones. There is game credit such as regular cash where you can buy stuff from the market, theres GC, which you can pretty just exchange it for cash.... since the whole market uses cash... but what is other purpose of GC you ask? To revive your character and open up private server. Not much to really explain here.  Map itself is not really huge as DayZ but its actually a good scaling, meaning is so huge nor that empty, most of the building is enterable, so you can camp or find a spot to hide. Since DayZ is one time chance of survival and your loot could be gone at that time if you got killed, this game have \"Personel Locker\" (Moving Item placement) and \"Global Inventory\" (your personel item placement), so you can litterally collect and keep your items in it, making it a hassle free to go out and do anything. but it somehow falls really flat due to its huge amount fail on the developer team and support team, trust me, is not even pleasant. Got something missing or stuck? no â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ given. Accidently deleted your character? No one gives a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. Need help on the games, NO. ONE. â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. GIVES.  If you are a fan of Totalbiscuit, AngryJoe and other famous reviewers, seen some rant and such, it feels like this is a piece a â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, but is not really that huge piece of â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, its playable and enjoyeble with your zombie killing friends and such. Would I recommend this game? Maybe. Should you buy this game over DayZ? Nah. It all depends on you, whether to play it or not. Score = 6/10 ( +Its a zombie mmorpg game, +Habit of looting, +The Feeling of the survival, +Crap tons of weapons, +Vault system to keep all the items you loot, +Fun playing people, -PVP community is abit abused, so be careful first-timer, -No PVE, -Marketplace is expensive, -Horrible support team, -Private servers are costly )", "appid": "226700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077032965", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1381492800.0}
