{"text": "The flow of gameplay gets interrupted way too often for an unecessary cutscene, and it feels wrong. I'd welcome the addition of moving while aiming down sights if I could use it for longer than a minute without getting interrupted by a cutscene. Kicking doors in RE5 were game actions that barely broke the flow of gameplay. In RE6, it's a cutscene. This also makes the PVP a pain to play since you can't set yourself up in a strategic position while the human players are in a cutscene. Did I mention there were cutscenes? If you liked the RE movies more than the games, you might like this one. Otherwise, don't buy it. I refunded it after the gameplay time shown on this review, wasn't worth my $8.49 I paid for the complete edition (did I mention the DLC playlists are dead?).", "appid": "221040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019694993", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1496145600.0}
