{"text": "Well, the tiny MP community that the game does have, are actually â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥... The game has this ridiculous way to \"save your cash\" in stashes but if you get killed and go and pick it up and someone sees you, theyll just blow you up to take ur â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥. The vehicles are super lame, the mecanics are ok, but they are bland and it's not explained how they are mustered and why. More or less, here more troops, more vehicles, go shoot! And the shooting is â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ endless. Coop or single player is basically endless horde mode. Taking a single objective takes numerous hours as the enemy just throws endless waved of soldiers at you (sometimes this anti-climactically takes secons, like 3 almost empty bases in a row). They AI not particularly \"bright\" but not too bad. They take cover when shot at, take rooftops, try to flank, but have weird quirks like lumping behind a rock or swimming beneath the docs for no apparent reason. But the machine gun fire is constantly mowing them down and they never stop... Its ANNOYING AS â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥, because it can only be fun for so many hours as you are trying to take A SINGLE OBJECTIVE doing the exact same thing.  The little items you get as loot occasionally, that you can sell for cash, is a broken system that gets abused by people who just buy shields and run around picking up all the loot. If you are a sniper, or focused on actually winnning the battle, good luck making money off the battle, more than likely for your efforts you will be killed by the enemy and then if that happens enough times, your resources are 0 and you cant affort to arm yourself with anything other than a basic rifle, while every tool is running around with a shield and full armor, swimming in cash... (its not like that all the time, but i've seen it more than once)  Also Im not sure about this, but there is no way to \"unlock\" new guns that arent standard stock. You can find them and i guess trade them, but if you die or some douchebag thinks he wants your gun he'll just rpg you... Well, thats that. If i'm wrong, someone correct me Overall, the game is fun, I had about 2 days of fun with it, but at the current stage, I feel like that is all it can offer 99% of players. There's just not that much here, besides a robust foundation. There are maybe 30-50 people that are not part of that majority. More development and balancing, ability to pick maps, actual PVP, a tutorial (after all this time i still feel like im missing like 70% of data) and maybe some â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ character customization, and i wouldnt mind actually playing this with my friends. But for now, thumbs down...", "appid": "270150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198045737254", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466510400.0}
