{"text": "This game is one of the most beautiful games I've seen; the mix of a Lovecraftian aesthetic with the beautiful, hand-drawn visuals of Jotun is something that is undoubtedly pleasing to the eye. Also, I didn't find the controls near as bad as a lot of people say they were. I found them intuitive, having lots of variety to ways to combo things together, and being smooth and well-thought out. However, that's where the good things end. Despite looking & feeling wonderful to play, the actual areas you'll be playing through have some of the most backward design you have EVER seen. enemies show up in droves wherever you go, sometimes even spawning endlessly. There were points where there was an enemy with a ranged attack off-screen, and when I went to the spot they were at to fight them, another would immediately spawn where I JUST was, off-screen, turning the fight into nothing more then the most tedious back and forth. There were points where, while trying to do a tense jumping puzzle, the game would just spawn enemies that weren't even native to the area I was in, endlessly, making it a chore to even attempt the puzzle. This is 100% a wonderful game to watch someone play, but a nightmare to play itself.", "appid": "535480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061963873", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567166400.0}
