{"text": "The game had a promising start.  Very bioshockey.  The shooting mechanics were meh, but so was Bioshock's. The game locked me into a kill-box with an un-ending supply of spawning monsters and it gave me the hint to \"find an alternate way in.\"  The alternate way was obvious, a locked doorway but I could not find out how to open it..  Then suddenly, it opened on it's own.  It was then I realized what the trigger for this \"puzzle\" was;  You run out of ammo and depleat your healthpacks.  When you are limping to your death, the door opens on it's own.  It was the \"he's suffered enough\" tripwire. It was at this point that I noticed the number of remaining f#cks I had to give began to deplete rapidly.  Three minutes later the game put me in similar situation.  At this point, I was completely out of f#cks to give.  I was forced to quit and uninstall the game.  Such a shame that my inventory was so limited.  Maybe your experience will be better than mine.", "appid": "42670", "steamid": "profiles/76561197993437321", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603627200.0}
