{"text": "This game is not really great from what I expected it to be. Story was unique, different than the other games I played, but it was too \"overdone\" in my opinion. I can't spoil the story just yet since the game just came out and I don't want to ruin it for the others. If I had to mention about the story, you would be more or less disappointed. The reason why I gave this game a negative review is because it was sort-of repetitive exploration and eventually starting to bore me. What it gave me was: Flashbacks after Flashbacks, Tunnels after Tunnels, Corridors after Corridors, Caves after Caves, you get it. The puzzles were done too easy that I figured them out in just few seconds. The new \"struggle\" mechanic after losing your mind in the dark was more of a nuisance than a dangerous situation. Inventory was being very limited, preventing you to take more oil canisters/matches. Unskippable cutscenes. Also one lost mind can cause cheap jumpscares to you (flashing pictures and noise). And few other minor bugs. One or two things I liked about this game was the atmosphere and the new addition to the matches. The matches allows you to light up multiple light sources (like lanterns, torches or candles) with only one match and use it as a small light source. Pretty handy, but like I said earlier, the inventory space ruins it. Being able to hold 10 matches at once isn't really great considering how quick they can ran out which ruins my immersion with this game. The atmosphere in the other hand is great. The skies were pretty in the deserts, the caves look terrifying, ambient noise all over the places. Monsters growling. These things kept me back when I was playing TDD in 2012. Good times. Overall, the game isn't good or great for me. Other people might share their different opinions, but me, I am just disappointed with this game. I just hope that the next Amnesia game could be better. *grammar", "appid": "999220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198024680817", "voted_up":