{"text": "Update #2: A few months later, and the links posted below now take you to blank pages on the Playstation Store. That is absolutely crazy. Update: I've been farming for over ten hours. It's pretty bad, and it didn't need to be this way. You'd have to be insane to find this fun. Look at what these developers did in other regions on the PS Vita: They're selling a low-level weapon that can be farmed on the first level of the Dungeon of Trials for the equivalent of $4.00 USD. Here's another: This is the best weapon in the game for lords, that takes hours of farming, available for the almighty dollar -- and it's cheaper than the Bushido Blade! The drop rates in this game were clearly engineered to drive people crazy and tempt them into shelling out more money. It's made even worse by a difficulty spike midway into the game that, although passable, is still a transparent attempt to compound the frustration caused by this exploitative design. I doubt they adjusted anything when they brought it to Steam, so we just get to deal with it. Developers need to stop doing this. I'm thumbing this down, but if I could use my middle finger, I would. I deleted my original review. I neither disagree nor agree with it at this point. But I'd feel guilty talking someone into buying LoLS knowing how much farming is involved and why it was probably made this way.", "appid": "948640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198047561118", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595678400.0}
