{"text": "It is evident that a lot of care was put into properly honoring the subjects and culture the game was inspired by; the insights you collect and watch throughout the game was my favourite part. But, when the best part of a game is its optional lore videos, you must seriously question the core gameplay. It is seriously lackluster, to say the least. I would even go as far as to say that the platforming ruins the game; it is not just a minor inconvenience, as the platforming is atrocious and adds absolutely nothing to the storytelling. For me, it got to a point where I concidered giving up on finishing the game. However, I sat through the rest, mainly to watch the remaining insights and get the achievements, while still wishing Never Alone would redeem itself in the end. Sadly, it never did, and my frustration with the gameplay weighs much heavier than the charming art and lore.", "appid": "295790", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063976966", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517313600.0}
