{"text": "Dead in Bermuda is a survival/pseudo-strategy game with good premise but also with too many issues. PROS: + It has some novel ideas. + Graphic and UI design is clean. CONS: - Too many balancing issues. Too hard on normal, too easy on easy setting. - Boring story. Story progression is shallow. Characters are bland and uninspired. - Tone of voice. It is neither funny nor dramatic. Tries to capture both and fails on both end miserably. - Variety of things. Everything feels the same. - Zero replay value if you finished it once. FINAL: 4/10 It has some novel ideas there and there. It feels like an unfinished, unpolished concept. Pass this one, doesnt worth your time.", "appid": "384310", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009654132", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603713600.0}
