{"text": "Just don't buy it There are plenty of survival horror games that are much better. This game is broken in so many ways, just look at the forums tons of users who can't even play. I am able to run it for what that's worth, but the controller support is still lacking. Also the devs really (from what I have seen others might have a different response) don't seem to think they need to fix anything. I have seen post by devs where they basically blamed the users (not flat out implied) for buying a game their system can't run. But that's the thing a lot of these systems should be able to run it and it just doesn't work. If you have a really good DX11 computer and feel like rolling the dice be my guest, but I say wait and see if the devs actually release any updates. Hasn't been one for at least a few months and the game only came out in April I think there was one in May. Update: It really falls short on gameplay there are many other survival horror games that do a much better job at suspense. It has an orginal idea, but it's not enough to break off from games like Slender, Amnesia, and Outlast. A lot of the scary stuff has literally been used in these other games and the effect is just getting tiresome.  There are lots of complaints from users about lag. Threads with hundreds of posts, and then you have to listen to people tell you that your computer is not really DX11 and you don't really know what you are doing.  Even if you getting running without lag chances are you are not going to play it that much, after all it is just walking down halls the whole time.  Just take a look at the other reviews and some posts on the forums chances are you will turn away and run screaming from this game.", "appid": "230840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198023511353", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1406289600.0}
