{"text": "I. An uncompelling and bland attempt at recreating a legendary game, visibly following the modern action RPG tendencies. There is a multitude of issues with it like the technical flaws, and the apparent 'reimagining' of the story and atmosphere, which will undoubtedly face lots of reproach from the fans. Yet, there is way more to it. The very attitude toward this game's development feels horribly off judging by what I have experienced. Surely, it is important to cater to the general playerbase that exists today, but there is already enough games that do that, not to mention that they will inevitably be ahead in terms of graphics, combat, story - you name it. With this approach, the game is doomed to blend with other generic RPGs we already have - hardly contributing anything to the longevity of Gothic series. Then, what can be done about it? Gothic does deserve a remake, but it should be mainly focused on meticulously bringing back the experience the original game had. Yes, there is plenty room for adjustments, but nothing should be changed SO drastically. Gothic had unique controls and combat system, which should be actually preserved to some extent. A good way would be sticking to Gothic 2, where controls were actually rather intuitive, no longer requiring at least 2 inputs for most of the actions.  The gameplay should also be as close to the original game as possible. That includes the game balance, the equipment and its impact on player's abilities, the magic system, to name just a few. All these features are vital for the game, for they comprise a considerable portion of the Gothic experience. Without them, it will end up being a mere travesty, just a boring imitation of the masterpiece that is Gothic.  Same goes for the atmosphere, the graphics, the music and everything else. Thankfully, Gothic has seen an incredible amount of improvement. Not only by the developers themselves, but also by the fans, who are to this day interested in the Gothic series. There are numerous mods that improve and expand the original experience, and many are still being made. However, everything has its limits, and there is only so much one can improve in some of the game aspects, mostly due to the game engine limitations. However, an actual developer should have more power to accomplish such things. This might be asking too much, but it is what the game truly needs. II. Pros: â€¢The possibility of a remake itself, as well as the possibility of the issues getting fixed. â€¢Territorial expansion is nice, and some of the areas look very authentic, like the Old camp. â€¢Apparent restoration of the cut content, like feeding animals and stuff, since there is a lot of unfinished things in the original game. Generally, this is a good direction for change. â€¢Graphics. Although it is a questionable one. Graphics play a significant role in building up the atmosphere, which is a key feature for Gothic, therefore it should be treated carefully. â€¢Controller support. Cons: â€¢Combat system. Although it does have a vibe of the original one, it should be even more so, in order to keep the one-of-a-kind feeling it once had. â€¢Equipment. Hopefully, the current armor models are just placeholders, they look completely different from the original now, while it should be the other way around. The weapons should also look realistic, since that was an important feature in Gothic. No thick blades, gigantic cross guards - that kind of stuff. â€¢Balance. Should stick closer to the original, while not necessarily being exactly the same. It was impossible to defeat, say, a snapper in the very beginning of the game. Attack and defense stats were a paramount factor in a fight. If the damage is lower than defense, there would be no damage at all. It was a simple system, but with it the stats actually mattered a lot. â€¢Dialogue. There is a bit too much chatter, compared to the concise and on point dialogue of the original. Also the fading into black for every dialogue kind of breaks the flow of the game, it is just excessively showy. â€¢Voice acting. It is just flawed, the phrases have a lot of unnecessary pauses, and also don't always match the subtitles. â€¢UI. I would rather have a more simple one; also the \"4-directional\" dialogue UI is uncalled for, it probably ever really works when the choices are contrasting to each other, but that is not the case here. â€¢Other minor stuff. Like the technical issues, animations, music and whatnot. These are still a vital part of overall experience, which will hopefully be polished to a decent degree.", "appid": "950670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065117839", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "92", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576238400.0}
