{"text": "This is an updated review in light of a new announcement that Gamigo has posted on May 21st where they have decided to do a business model bait and switch from what they've originally promised. There's plenty of big glaring issues already before this happened which you will read in my review but this news tops it. The original Archeage under Trion (before Gamigo bought them) had bait and switch issues as well, unfortunately this is the same wolf just with new sheep's clothing.  Before I mention actual game issues, let's talk about the customer support for a second. Customer Support is almost non existent as tickets will literally go months without any kind of response. I've dealt with a lot of gaming companies and Gamigo's customer support is easily one of the worst out there. Archeage Unchained according to their financial report is their number 1 game for revenue, yet they can't get a support team to answer tickets? There's absolutely no reason in 2020 to have such piss poor customer service, it's disgraceful and an embarrassment.  Now onto to a few huge issues that the game has. The servers suffer from daily stability issues from disconnects to multiple crashes every day. While something like this can be a pain in any game you play it can be extremely devastating in this game due to trade runs. A crash or disconnect during a trade run can result in the loss of hundreds to over a thousand gold. Most dungeons have a limited amount of entries you can have each day, if it happens during one of those runs you lose an entry. Losing large amounts of gold and these needed dungeon runs to gear up hurt, especially in a game like this. Besides the server issues there's plenty of bugs when it comes to the UI, audio, graphics and one of the biggest item systems in the game, the Archepass. The communication between Gamigo and XL Games is dreadful and patches often go out very buggy despite known issues, sometimes even game breaking ones. Sometimes it can take months to get fixes to the major issues in the game. Another one of the big problems is that the game's population is on a steady decline, losing hundreds of players each month on both Steam and non Steam players. While you can't view the population that doesn't use Steam you can see the Steam players on   which is now under 800 peak players in the last 24 hours from this review. Even on the most populated servers you'll find it hard to find any kind of party or raid to do dungeons and other content. Even the faction war that is across every server sometimes can't even find enough players to run. I want to point out something that makes this situation with the population even worse. Most players own at least 2 or 3 accounts due to not being able to create more than 2 characters and these extra accounts are part of total population numbers. The server populations are low already which is why I don't understand why they would decide to launch a new \"fresh start\" server which will only pull people away from existing servers. One of the biggest red flags to stay away from the game is that there's a large portion of the game's population who buy gold for not just themselves but also for friends and guild members on a constant basis. What's even worse is that Gamigo is aware of the issue and does nothing about it. Being in an open world PVP MMORPG it's hard to compete or even just stay alive when you have to go against people who are purchasing gold and killing you in 1 attack even with high gear scores. Going up against players who buy gold who can just one hit you no matter how much legit work or time you put into the game just isn't fun. There's way too many red flags to recommend this game no matter what the price tag is. If you are considering getting Archeage Unchained I would strongly recommend finding another game to invest your time in. To my friends who have this game on their Steam wishlist do yourself a huge favor and take a moment and remove this game from there.", "appid": "1147660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198075883037", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "18", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576152000.0}
