{"text": "As a game, the game itself- it's really incredible. When I owned this on Xbox, it was one of my favorite games at the time and was one of the best experiences I had playing a horror (well thrilling action horror) video game. However, after all this time, playing it on Steam ... I just can't recommend it. It crashes so very often. Unless you're one of the few who got lucky, my game kept crashing at random, no matter what I did. My graphics card is at it's best, I downloaded programs suggested to me by Reddit and other Steam Forums to help the game stabilize but unfortunately, the port to Steam made the game unable to stay active for too long. It will crash whenever it pleases, whether nothing is happening or a lot is happening, there's no pattern. So this is likely due to feeling outdated, but the controls feel very stiff. They tried to copy Resident Evil 4's mechanics and while it felt good years ago, it hasn't aged well. Most of the time enemies will get a drop on you simply because your movements are limited, and you're stuck facing one way until you're able to turn around but it may be too late by that point. Everything else from guns, to powers, to the enemy AI and mechanics is all great. Just the movement and limitations of the player hurts the game for me now. Having the game on full windows made it unpleasing to look at. I had to decrease it into a smaller window to appreciate the game visually, otherwise things are stretched out and look bad with the quality dropping. There aren't any options to help fix the resolution, even by manually doing so through your graphics driver / program. Amazing story, amazing atmosphere, sound is god tier, enemies and gameplay mechanics are incredible, the story is very interesting and draws you in, and the game overall is just a masterpiece in terms of being a well structured game. If you want to play this game, play it on the console, not on Steam / PC. I believe the port went poorly and the game suffered as a result, losing stability and I couldn't bear to play any longer after Chapter 2 from the constant crashing or random hiccups. Love the game, hate the version on Steam is why I can't recommend it.", "appid": "17470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046999341", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602849600.0}
