{"text": "Where do I start? I bought this game around the date of release, played for 100 hours or so and for no particular reason forgot about it for a while. I  wanted to come back to it but they started releasing paid DLC after paid DLC and although the game seemed fun, I am not someone who is able to afford to pay hundreds of $ just for DLCs in one game so I had to quit. I got back into the game around the time they released Ultimate Edition, which seemed like a great deal: you pay for it, get access to all the game content and get all the future content for free.  You can see by my hours that I played this game a lot and I had a lot of fun despite all the bugs, questionable (to say the least) balance choices, performance issues, awful cheater situation etc. And while I wasn't playing the game during that time, lets not forget about the whole microtransaction scandal they had in 2015(?) when they added paid skins after they promised that they would not. Many people quit that day. Today, months after they announced that payday 2 development ended, after the story was finally concluded, they announced that  . What does that mean for the game? There will be more content, obviously. It also means that they lied once again, that all the people who paid for ultimate edition were lied to and scammed. They even admit to it as you can read in the announcement I linked \"Now weâ€™re breaking the Ultimate Edition promise of forever-free-content\". Besides all that it also means that the story   get ruined for the sake of shoving as much paid DLC down our throat as possible, that the game balance might be affected even further, that the people who spent hundreds, thousands of hours completing the game with all achievements, trophies as such might   pay for MORE DLC to unlock certain achievements (don't forget that in payday 2 achievements that require you to use a specific DLC weapon are common). They are about to milk their fan base with DLC content, shoving as much of it as they can and as fast they can, after promising they would do no such thing. And of course there are always the people saying this kind of stuff: \"lol are you complaining about more content?\", \"just don't buy it\" and most importantly \"they need the money man\" That is no excuse to lie and scam the fanbase that stuck with the game through all the bs and keep in mind  If you are the kind of person to throw money at a company after they spat in your face good on you but they are in the financial situation they are in due to their poor choices, making games that no one asked for and the fanbase shouldn't be the one to pay for their failures.  I have had a lot of fun in the game, made many friends too and I am contemplating quitting out of principle, we will see what the future holds. For now I can not recommend anyone to spend money on this game. I apologize for any spelling mistakes.", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072390053", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "566", "votes_funny": "63", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1572004800.0}
