{"text": "LOL wtf was this... First of all, I am a HUGE Halo PC fan. I grew up playing the first halo on the PC, as well as the second and I fell  in love with both games, especially the first. When I heard a new Halo game was finally coming out for the PC, I was excited. Unfortunately I found out it wasn't a multiplayer Halo, instead it was just a port of a mobile game, but I still gave it a chance. I regret doing so. This game is a extremly generic top-down shooter with halo skins and sounds added on... That's it. The story is short, lame, boring, and dull. It's just a few cutscenes, some voiceovers and boxes of text....... Missions get repetitive and boring very early in the game. Also, no co-op... even though the Xbox One version has it. While the game is only $5, all it really is a time killer game. If microsoft can give us this Halo, then they can give us Halo 3. 5/10 = Average.", "appid": "277430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041332440", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "94", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1396699200.0}
