{"text": "I liked this game, despite all the bugs and the dumpster fire it is, I enjoyed it. I played it all the way through to post campaign with one of the builds that actually functions properly. There are MANY bugs in this game that ruin the experience.  bosses falling through the floor summons dont work properly there are passive skills that dont work  there are modifiers for active skills that dont work your progress can be reset at any time your stash items can vanish online still doesnt fully function numerous crashes bugs that impede story progress (doors not opening when they should) the way stats and levels scale, you lose your investment by leveling up, look at agility, you wind up losing   attack speed every time you level up, so just to keep the same attack speed bonus you had you have to keep dumping points into it. at that point why not just dump everything into a flat bonus like toughness for hp? The balance because of this is pretty bad I found that with all these bugs that harm you, there is also a bug with gems to increase their value and get tons of gold. of course after some of my items vanishing, i figured what the heck i can use that to buy more stuff in return. Then the devs post this \"Gold/item dupe: We would like to inform you that we will fix the gold/item dupe issues later this week. Actions will also be taken against accounts who abused these issues or took advantage of it.\" THE GAME DOESNT FUNCTION and thats what you choose to focus on???? Are you kidding me? Everything that is wrong with this game and I abuse a bug to try to get a small amount of enjoyment out of this trash and the result is \"actions will be taken\". I get that the bug should be patched, but out of everything wrong with this game, fixing that particular bug and \"actions will be taken\" absolutely should not take priority over a functioning game. At this point, banning me for abusing a bug in single player would be a favor", "appid": "424370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067247951", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581940800.0}
