{"text": "7/7/2019: It's worse now, refund! ORIGINAL REVIEW: Okay so I did come into this expecting it to be somewhat bad due to the reviews and the demo being broken and so just being a menu preview which is bad looking and working. BUT the actual gameplay is bad as I was hoping for improvements particularly I was looking forward to the YouTube integration however that is done poorly. That is not the only thing though as the song generation and the mode comparison between audio surf 1 and 2 is confusing as it seems like audio surf 2 is actually an early version of audio surf 1 in terms of....well EVERYTHING. I'm not saying that audio surf 1 is then an final version in comparison to 2 as the menus could have used more work but at least the gameplay was solid. Anyway consider this a summary. The YouTube integration is what I was hoping for was you could maybe link your YouTube account or open up a YouTube window or something like that to find songs you've wanted to play but couldn't download them or buy them to get them...etc etc....it was not that and instead popular songs and then pasting a YouTube URL and YouTube search. I didn't try the YouTube URL but I did look at popular songs and YouTube search which were both disappointing as the search was a joke...as instead of YouTube search results where you get a ton of results and then something like what you typed in (even with bad spelling), you get barely ANY results and none of them were even looking like what I typed in and some were gameplays of an map named similar to the artist. Next up is the song generation so I'll explain the settings I had the game set to in terms of the mode and skin which was mono classic and mono where you have the duplicate which \"hits everything\". Also by song generation I mean how the game decides where the blocks you come across are placed. I played Caravan Palace Lone Digger 4 times, first two times were in audio surf 2 where the first one was the YouTube integrated version and then the version I got from my downloaded version of it, the last two times were in audio surf 1 where I only played the start in mono and stopped to switch to mono pro. Anyway in audio surf 2 I noticed a BIG difference in terms of the generation in the beginning when you just start and the build up to the first drop and at the time I wasn't even looking for it as I was just testing out my mouse sensitivity. But due to the difference I then tried in audio surf 1 which was again different but even more so as it made me realize that there's no difficulty settings making new players struggle with getting to grips with the game as there's a lot more blocks in 2 than 1 and they are spaced closer together as  a result, oh and yes mono pro and mono are different in generation but mono pro BUILDS upon mono's generation by making some blocks bad and adding in a few but to not the point in audio surf 2. Anyway the only similarity in song generation that I PERSONALLY noticed was that audio surf's 1 generation of mono and mono pro were somewhat similar while 2's was completely different and that was from me changing the file source from YouTube to the mp3 file I have. Anyway I'll move on as I'll be repeating myself a lot if I continue with generation so I'll go onto the menu's and why I feel that audio surf 2 is an early version of 1. Simplicity and usability is my simple reason as 2 has a lot more with it's menu's of having everything split up into different tabs and sections within sections making it not so simple to find the folder finder and then start using it along with knowing even if it's loading the folder or not which takes a long time. When you get to the folder with the songs in it as well you are greeted with just a pure mess with trying to understand what is what as I may have songs that weren't brought and so downloaded which have then long names but even the normal length ones were encountering this issue of where the name went OUTSIDE the name box and some even went overlapping the song over. It's like Window's icon view just where instead of the name text wrapping downwards it goes into the next item area to cover up it's name, but there's no way to change that view and the order is alphabetical so that's your only hint as to where you are in song searching. Now the settings menu was all in one but the sliders seemed broken at first as I couldn't move them but then I found I needed to click to the left end of the slider to grip it making it rather annoying to change your mouse sensitivity even a bit precisely since it's a slider....but a hard to move one too. Oh and I needed to hit okay to just exit the menu, no undo button or cancel button if you mess up with your changes and escape key doesn't work. Finally when your playing the game you pause it through the escape key and you get a default unity like menu popping up which has the normal options that you would want though the options button takes you to the same options screen so if you dislike the skin you got at the time there's no way to change it without ending the song and changing skin before making sure you had the right song selected as sometimes it changed to the next song in my folder list. Now if I compare this to audio surf 1 everything is an improvement on 2 as the folder system is first off not the Window's icon view but the details view however still just the names but if the name is too long the text seems to scale down or expand the window but for that you need VERY long names. The rest of the menu apart from the settings are all in one simple kind of as there's a lot less in terms of features (no steamworkshop accessibility ingame) but there's a lot more clearness in terms of difficulty of the mode you are selecting due to the colour of the sections and the names of them along with iron man mode box right at the bottom to be ticked for a harder challenge. You can still change the themes and so on from audio surf 2 but it's all in one settings screen which you can just press escape to get into and out of while playing a song and the changes are IMMEDIATE it's still sliders for the mouse sensitivity but the sound effects for the hitting of the blocks is changeable of the sound and can be set to nothing as well without turning off other sound effects, in 2 that's not possible at all. There's also less modes in audio surf 2 than 1 or what feels to be less due to the fact that in 1 there was maybe 5-10 modes just under different difficulty names (mono-mono pro-mono ninja) and then there's iron man mode you can turn on and then do all of the modes again with it on for extra difficulty for them for extra points. However as a result of the song generation and the modes in 2 I feel like the points value have less value overall than 1 as again Lone Digger song I got 35,000 ish personal best currently in audio surf 1 while in 2 I easily managed I think 550,000? That's an huge difference but I don't really understand how the point system works in 2 though in 1 it's simple as each colour block you hit doubles the points you get from colour blocks (starting from 1) to a maximum of 240 but hitting a grey block resets it. A small extra thing that I dislike which is kinda of a menu issue is that in audio surf two the mode you select has a very very rough text as to what is going on in it but before you actually start the song you get a preview of 3 screenshots of kinda of what to expect while explaining any abilities. But in 1 there is a tool tip for the mode you are about to and even a tutorial which I personally prefer though it's hard to compare the modes of the two due to the fact that mono classic in audio surf 2 seems nothing like any of the mono's in audio  surf 1 as none of them had a duplicate hitting everything for you but did have a jump button or the ability to go into side lanes to get a break from the action and just ride the song.  PS Graphics in 2 are better than 1 arguably only due to workshop. Now to refund for Â£4", "appid": "235800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077990240", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514289600.0}
