{"text": "$hitty game! Cash grab AF , there's nothing really special about this game except some of the moments ! It has some inconsistencies with season 1 as well :| again your choices don't matter as it was for season 1 ! Let me tell you about their biggest lie : \"Multiple endings depending on the choices you make\" ( it's on store page of the game don't say you lied to us! ) Here are things i can understand after i read this quote : 1. They cut most of the things including endings 2. Maybe it was a hype for players to buy the game lel 3. They said \"Mulitple Endings\" instead of  \"different cutscenes\"   Until episode 2 I thought this game is a masterpiece and it was way too good for a prequel then i played episode 3 ... $hitty , rushed , feeling that some things are cut from the game ,  giving more important roles to minor characters. Game itself fools everyone with interesting gameplay elements but at the end of game , you realize there's nothing special about story because new gameplay elements blinded you! I remember something that Zak Gariss ( Lead Writer of the game ) said this game is about how you want to build your relationship with rachel which I understood something : endings = intimacy points you have made through all episodes but it seems they all get cut from the game! Also fandom is going to be a toxic fandom because majority of the fans are shipping this person to that person but I didn't see anyone talking about plot and how awful the plot is! About Deluxe Edition : Bunch of outfits or better to say skins :| A short and repetitive episode Mixtape mode  --------------------------------------------------------------------- - Outfits = 3 outfits : Punk doe ( worst of all because it's not suitable for chloe she looks like a W-H-O-R-E with that outfit ) - Hawt Dawg Man ( WTF what a silly name ) is childish - Illuminati : Good one because it reminds me of chloe of season 1 and also it's suitable for her ... but most disappointing thing is characters won't have reactions to these outfits! - Mixtape mode : same cinematic scene where chloe smokes and licensed music plays with organizing your playlist :| Stupidest thing , You can either download songs or listening to them via spotify  - Bonus Episode called Farewell : short and it was just reciting things that already have been mentioned in season 1 and before the storm and it has some inconsistencies too for example joyce being a smoker and that wasn't implied in both games except in season 1 in alternative reality she was a smoker not in normal reality and of course I remember something from season 1 that max said william didn't finish painting the house and it was kinda half way work and william died but farewell plot is set the day that william died and you can see william didn't even paint the house :| like I said they mentioned same things more and more that made me bored AF :/ for instance william's death ... I expected something new in this episode like how max and chloe became friends with each other and more stories about them or i expected side activities such as playing new games or even playing video games in episode. It wasn't emotional or sth because of things I mentioned thing aboved ^ The last scene of farewell is also $hitty!  why? because both max and chloe didn't act in season 1 that this tape even exists and lack of emotional scenes... By the way , if you didn't buy this game don't buy it . buy some other indie games like inside , oxenfree and games like that not this piece of crap :/ 3/10 NOT RECOMMENDED", "appid": "554620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198277349905", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1508846400.0}
