{"text": "In short, I dislike the game because of its frustrating and confusing experience from some undesirable mechanisms. I play games to have a smooth and enjoyable experience, not to relive similar frustrations or challenges encountered in real life. The game doesn't satisfy my need.  The 6th reason I listed below has spoiler by the way. The story is nice, but there are a few flaws make the game much more less enjoyable as follows: 1. The option selection is extremely clumsy, this is particularly troublesome when I faced multiple choices, in the later investigation stage for example. I mean the cursor seems to be frozen in a very small area, so you can't freely move it around when there are multiple options. I mistakenly selected the wrong option countless times due to the clumsiness of this â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ system, other than my judgement.  2. The game lacks proper prompts as the instruction for next action. One thing makes me particularly annoying is when there's no guidance/objective to prompt my action. And there are so many times I didn't know what to do in this game, even hours after playing it.  3. Too many â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ puzzles. I play games to relax, not to think hard like when I work or study! This sort of game is more focused on the plot, not solving puzzles.  4. The rewind mechanism quickly loses its charm once you familiarize with it. Basically, it's just trial-and-error/SL trick.  5. It the only game I know that can't show up main menu after pressing \"ESC\". One replacing way is to press \"Alt + Tab\" by the way.  Another confusing experience.  6. When Chloe found Rachel's dead body, why was the music so â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ happy? This is so not immersive! It completely ruined the vibe there! These issues have one thing in common: they greatly disrupt/slow the game pace/progress. So what I feel is I spent so much time dealing with something relatively unimportant, which resulted in much slower progress in the game. Intuitively, I felt the game is very tiresome to play, because I spent much time on it, while the progress was very slow. I wish it could have the mechanism like Telltales, except there are valid consequences for each selection.", "appid": "319630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124872187", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1563710400.0}
