{"text": "Despite spending over 600 hrs in this game, and currently being in Infamy 10th, PAYDAY 2 had its good times and bad times. Basically a love/hate relationship with this game.  Pros - - You get to play in many different heists, special contracts, and levels - Community still offers minor updates every once in a while - Extreme amounts of availability for customizations on your character and weapons - Leveling up, especially being promoted to further Infamy levels feels rewarding, along with the after-match rewards you gain by securing loot (money/coke/etc.) - A few memes can happen occasionally anywhere. Who doesn't love them?? - Certain players can end up liking this game so much, to the point they grind a lot or consider this one of their favorite games to be somewhat-addicted to. Cons -  - Getting disconnected while in-game during a few occasions, which can be insanely frustrating. - You're going to get judged or treated harshly by players who are more experienced than you (with the purpose of them wanting to assure success to matches without any issues or fails from other players) - Expect to get kicked or even banned by a lobby's host for reasons, like taking too long to load, making issues, so on, so forth (related to previous con) - When playing a level in STEALTH, there will always be people that mess up, which annoys other players. (Though this can be adjusted in this host's lobby settings, including the addition of desired restrictions) - PAYDAY 2 can end up lacking constant taste for some players, as the game seems repetitive with the same usual playable level and contents, and that the game doesn't look like it ever changes much, especially from some updates. It's pretty much going to make players feel like this is the same game over and over, as soon as they launch it. - The game's repetitiveness and minimum appeal to players will make PAYDAY 2 seem like a boring, dry, and worthless game in certain times, and not worth wasting time on. - Adding on to the previous con, you're basically going to end up playing the same heists and stuff over and over again everyday you hop on PAYDAY 2, for 80% of your playtime, without anything changing or seen as interesting. Overall, I know I may have bashed the game a bit too much, but it's my own personal thoughts about it. Like I said, PAYDAY 2 can be a love/hate product to players, depending on how everyone's taste over content is. If you enjoy the usual feel of the game, go for it. If you can't seem to be interested CONSTANTLY, because of how the game slowly dies and feels dry on you, then don't waste time hopping on.", "appid": "218620", "steamid": "profiles/76561198292069452", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "290", "votes_funny": "40", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1577016000.0}
