{"text": "Pros: Beautiful cockpit, fantastic sound design, above average space combat. Cons: Lacks context, incomplete features, feels like it's still in alpha, and worst of all; an awful payment model. For those of you who want the planetary landing feature, do not buy this game, you should buy the standalone/expansion/first season. Confused yet? Well this 'season' of expansions, Horizons, contains the base game. So if you bought this game, too bad, sucks for you because you're spending a lot more money than people who have only just become interested. Also,  at the time of writing, that's all Horizons contains. So they're making existing players pay a lot of money for the game they already own + one feature and an unspecified list of promised features. I don't think I'll be buying that without a major price reduction. There is a slight, emphasis on slight, loyalty bonus. This is not good enough. Next year it will be the same thing. A new expansion off the back of one semi-complete feature, a promise of good things to come and then an exploitation of the fanbase as they try and shift more units of the game.", "appid": "359320", "steamid": "profiles/76561197974304047", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1451476800.0}
