{"text": "Game is amazing. Absolutely love it. So, why the negative review? Simple.  1) The Devs abandoned it. 2) MASSIVE memory leak issues and no matter how much memory you have, it will eventually crash from this. Period. 3) The game is laggy as hell, even with my damn top of the line PC. (Figured a work around with this by building a LOT of storage units for items though). 4) The game is FULL of bugs and issues that cause your hearthlings (these are your citizens) to sometimes top doing their jobs, stop building, stop collecting, ect... for no reason and it wont tell you why with no way to fix it. The game is simply infuriating with all these issues. Spend an hour creating a building/bridge/anything, go to save the item you created so you can build it... the game locks up/crashes... over and over. As much as I WANT to love this game and WANT to recommend it, I simply can not. The game COULD have been one off the best city building games I ever played, but instead, the Devs simple dropped the ball and called the game finished. There is a VERY good modding community attempting to keep it alive, and doing one hell of a job... but the memory leak issues and lock ups and crashes simply ruin the experience of the game.", "appid": "253250", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996947462", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589889600.0}
