{"text": "----TLDR at the bottom.---- So this game has, or had, a lot of potential, but it appears the developers decided to do some scummy money making gimmicks. Shortly after the \"main release\" it became farm fest central. Then after release they did a PAID DLC to give you OPTIONS to make it more fun like it was before the main release. The game doesn't have a \"difficulty setting\" on the base game, but if you purchase DLC you can then \"control the game difficulty\"...what a shock. If that isn't enough you literally spend your entire time playing this game doing nothing but grinding food to eat. Yes that's right you have a hunger meter. Well that's normal in games right? Well normally yes, but the food meter in this one depletes VERY rapidly and I played as the character who had the lowest food meter depletion. I ate 3 pork roasts, 4 mashed pumpkin plates, mashed beans, some chicken and some other food all in the span of ONE in game day and my character was still hungry. How many tapeworms did you get crash landing into the land of Niffelheim? If I ate all that in one day and was still hungry I think I would go to see a doctor and find out where my food is going because it's obviously not going into my stomach to fill me up. That being said there are more things that can turn you off from wanting to play this game. Take it with a grain of salt as you will, but I'm reviewing and being completely honest here. It is a survival game and you are supposed to \"survive\" but even in a \"real life situation\" (yeah I know it's a game bear with me here) you wouldn't eat 20lb of food a day just to \"live\". Even as a Viking who fights a lot you spend more time in Niffelheim murdering animals to eat than you do actually dungeon delving and fighting monsters to reach Asgard / Valhalla. Why even bother at this point? Decent graphics for the style Decent sound effects and music (can hear wind blowing through trees and animal sounds are realistic) Decent combat system, but a bit clunky at times Interesting ideas behind some of the stories and goals Grind grind grind grind grind for food and grind some more until you starve to death anyways eventually because you didn't buy the DLC to make the game easier on you or give you difficulty controls Enemies hit you super hard early on and your weapons are pathetic so you don't stand much of a chance so you play the game of hit and run all day if you don't want to die If you die you get a \"mortal wound\" which lowers your max food bar (like you need that crap) and you can only remove it if you make an alchemy workstation or you happen to make it to the \"town\" and have enough gold to purchase it. So you spend all your coin on either potions to remove the debuff or on food just to stay alive. As I said before GRIND GRIND GRIND GRIND GRIND. Your early game tools break super quick and you need to farm a decent bit of materials to keep making them which puts you right back into grind central Controls make no sense at times. You chop trees using the build button, but you have an action button to pick things up, why not make chopping wood the same as the gathering action to eliminate confusion? Progress is constantly hindered by having to try to gather food and knowing which food fills you up the most and farming it best as you can to keep from starving to death and dying Lackluster replay value if you don't own DLCs since they can't bother to put settings into the base game to try to get more money out of you (which is a trap because oh you think you might like it if you could control the game more, but what if the DLC is lackluster for you too?) The AI bots can make your game even harder if you're struggling just to find food and survive with food in your belly making it more frustrating and not worthwhile to play too Hard to find decent co-op partners it seems Eat 100 chickens a day and you still might starve to death basically. You spend more time in this game farming food than you do trying to reach Valhalla. Makes you wonder how they keep the feast halls full of food if all the Vikings are eating 100 lbs a person per day. Feel sorry for the hunters who have to go gather the meat and veggies let alone the cook who doesn't get a break from cooking the pigs and other meat. Also the paid DLC option just to get the ability to \"modify the settings\" to make it more fun is scummy and money hungry. Developers who do this for AAA titles and other games only understand 1 thing. Not purchasing their games affects their wallet. When they go back to caring about gamers / players then they'll figure out what it is to be a truly good game developer again. Numerous people have commented about this in reviews and in the forums. What do the devs have to say? Buy the DLC to \"make your game more fun\". More like buy the DLC to make yourself look more like a fool. Avoid this game for now unless you can devote endless hours to farming meat to survive. Otherwise you'll get annoyed at the excessive grind in this game. Real life Vikings, from back in the day, if they saw this game would be very displeased and angry I'm sure. They wanted to be known as ferocious fierce survival warriors not gluttons eating 100 stuffed pigs a day. Sure they liked feasting, but this is way too excessive. Save 100 pigs and your money and don't purchase this game.", "appid": "351100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198216594040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603800000.0}
